workouts.title: Workout
workouts.introText:
Chris and Luke have stacked this workout with only the biggest bicep-pumping, tricep-kicking, vein-popping moves – all back to back. Bring the intensity and you'll feel the difference.


Don't increase your weight until you have the new moves totally locked down – make the tutorial your first stop.

groups.title: Warm-up
groups.summary: Start rolling out the curls to find your intensity.

exercises.title: Ezy bar standing curls (25% lifting weight)
Ezy bar standing curls (50% lifting weight)
Ezy bar standing curls (75% lifting weight)

groups.title: Round 1
groups.summary: Double curl variations will hit your biceps from all angles.

groups.title: Round 2
groups.summary: Tempo is key on these curls, so count it out.

groups.title: Round 3
groups.summary: Get set for supersets that will demand a lot from your triceps.

groups.title: Round 4
groups.summary: Stick with the cable machine to refine your shoulders and triceps.
